text: Briyani rice was flavourful and fluffy. Fried chicken was crispy and large for $8.50.

Reside in the Kopitiam corner, this Indian stall cam cooked a plate of delicious beehoon mee goreng. Added the chicken meat for a $6.50 meal. The noodle texture was good. Not soggy or too oily. The chicken meat tasted fresh and tender. Every part wasn't too salty which was the plus point.

Simply charge. Ordered 2 plain 1 egg but got charged 2 eggs 1 plain for 2 times continuously. Was on the trust system, so I never checked. Once detected and checked back to c.card transactions, I was charged the same previously, but it is too late because it has already passed. Also, sometimes they also tell there's no plain prata for the day and only have egg prata. But in fact, egg prata is just a plain prata topped with egg only ðŸ˜…

Was trying to order a takeout but it seems to me the boss (who appeared to be an old Chinese man) doesn't seem to be interested in accepting customers for his new business. I was queuing for a takeout (how long does it take to pack ready-made plain and egg pratas?) and he effectively chased me away, even before my turn.

His attitude as a business-owner is incredibly disappointing.

If I really really need Indian food, I will gladly travel to other places to get my fix, than to feed this man's wallet and ego.
2nd time buying prata from this stall. 2nd time also waited very long for the prata. Please change the staff! Or provide training to work efficiently.
